(Lesson Vocabulary) Tj
T*
(- Summary: The main topic being studied, understood here as summary writing condenses a) Tj
T*
(text into its essential points without unnecessary detail.) Tj
T*
(- Core Focus: The main idea the learner must understand in this lesson: main ideas,) Tj
T*
(concise expression, and omission of repetition.) Tj
T*
(- Application: The point where the explanation is used in practice, such as reducing a) Tj
T*
(passage into a few clear sentences.) Tj
T*
(- Common Error: A repeated learner difficulty in this topic, for example copying large) Tj
T*
(parts of the original text.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Common Mistakes) Tj
T*
(- Misunderstanding the core focus of Summary: main ideas, concise expression, and) Tj
T*
(omission of repetition.) Tj
T*
(- Copying large parts of the original text.) Tj
T*
(- Jumping to an answer without showing the steps or reasoning clearly.) Tj
T*
(- Practising Summary without checking whether the method matches the question being) Tj
T*
(asked.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
